          }
        },
        "text_LHGLnM": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Heel pain is a common condition where weight-bearing on the heel causes significant discomfort. There are two main categories of heel pain: <br/><br/>The first category is caused by overuse or repetitive stress, resulting from excessive impact on a specific foot area. This condition, often referred to as \"heel pain syndrome,\" can be triggered by shoes with low heels, a thinned-out fat pad in the heel area, or a sudden increase in activity. <br/><br/>The second category is Plantar Fasciitis, which is usually caused by a biomechanical issue such as overpronation (flat feet). The plantar fascia is a fibrous tissue band running from the heel bone through the midfoot and into the forefoot.</p>",
            "text_font": "body",
            "text_size": "subtext-md",
            "text_max_size": 32,
